parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag light flashes
the horn does not work
the cruise control does not work
the airbag sensor malfunctions
and the airbag does not deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes do not stop the car properly
the brakes need to be replaced frequently
and the brakes fail to function in an emergency situation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to extend to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal extends to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop
the brake light is illuminated on the dashboard
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop
the brake light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the brake pedal and gas pedal can cause interference, leading to unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The gas pedal is too close to the brake pedal
causing the toe to hit the accelerator when applying the brake
leading to unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to notify vehicle owners of a recall can lead to delayed or missed repairs, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle owners not receiving recall notifications
lack of transparency in the recall process
inconvenience and wasted time due to the recall process.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift gears
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle stalls
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag warning light to come on, which may indicate a faulty airbag system, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
the airbag sensor is faulty
the airbag system is malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire sensor can cause the tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) warning light to come on, which may indicate underinflated tires, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The TPMS warning light comes on
the tire sensor is faulty
the tire pressure is not accurately displayed.
